children.subject: I can't speak to 189, but 149 is quite a small class and was not webcasted when I took it in Fall 2017.

Just commenting on the grad school part of your question: Personally, I don't think having 189 on progress when you apply the grad school (assuming you apply during this coming fall) will drastically affect your chances of being admitting into graduate school program too much. So I would optimize the schedule based on your immediate academic interests.

history.content: You should try emailing the professors directly

Hi all,

I really want to take EECS 149 and CS 189 together next semester. The problem is, both classes have the exact same lecture time. Do you know if one of them will be webcasted and offer alternative exam? Or I have no choice but to move 189 to Spring instead?

I'm a rising senior. This will be my last chance to take 149. I also think it might be good to have 189 on my transcript when I'm applying to grad school as well, especially when I want to do ML, so I really don't want to move 189 to next Spring. I'm not sure if it really matters to have 189 on my transcript when applying, though. Can an adviser comment on this, please?

If I really need to move 189 to later, should I take CS 100 or 188 instead for the upcoming semester?

Any thought would be appreciated, please.

Thank you.
